# Build and Test Workflow

## Build Commands

- **Multi-package build**: `daml build --all` from repository root
- **Individual package build**:

  ```bash
  cd fungible-token
  daml build
  cd ../fungible-token-test
  daml build
  ```

## Test Execution

- **Run all tests**: `daml test --all` in [fungible-token-test/](/fungible-token-test/)
- **Specific test file**: `daml test --files daml/FungibleTokenTest.daml`
- **Test coverage**: Check [fungible-token-coverage](/fungible-token-test/fungible-token-coverage)

## Package Configuration

- [fungible-token/daml.yaml](/fungible-token/daml.yaml) - Main package configuration
- [fungible-token-test/daml.yaml](/fungible-token-test/daml.yaml) - Test package configuration
- [multi-package.yaml](/multi-package.yaml) - Multi-package build configuration

## Dependencies

- Splice API DARs in [dars/](/dars/) directory
- External test sources in [external-test-sources/](/external-test-sources/)
- Canton or Sandbox for running scripts

## Development Workflow

1. Make changes to implementation in [fungible-token/](/fungible-token/)
2. Update tests in [fungible-token-test/](/fungible-token-test/)
3. Build packages: `daml build --all`
4. Run tests: `daml test --all`
5. Update documentation as needed
